AU  - Gollier, Christian
T1  - A Note on Portfolio Dominance
PY  - 1997
Y1  - 1997/01/01
DO  - 10.2307/2971744
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 64
IS  - 1
SP  - 147
EP  - 150
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - In the standard portfolio problem, a shift in the distribution of the risky asset is “portfolio-dominated” if it reduces the demand for the risky asset by all risk-averse agents, irrespective of the risk-free rate. We show that the condition obtained by Landsberger and Meilijson (1993), while necessary, is not sufficient for portfolio dominance and we present an exact necessary and sufficient condition.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2971744
